32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.0633dafc-b74b-40ec-aae8-f13969965b24.description=This workflow returns the artifact's properties and values using Artifact APIs. result\: propertyNameValuesList\: pipe separated list of property name and values ( where each property name and values would be ; seprated and multiple values would be , seprated) e.g. - property 1; value1,value2|property 2; value3|property 3; value3,value4|........ 32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.0e0585fe-309d-4da3-a928-85e17a4d1758.prompt=Enter a value for value1 32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.1082a937-e0c0-4cbd-b756-f7d0dcd489ed.prompt=Artifact ID 32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.22ac4175-4316-4f1f-8bc5-58563c1c2e13.prompt=Service Component Id 32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.2a5e67a0-ea9e-498b-b4e7-651a67509cdb.prompt=User Identifier 32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.2bea90ee-08a2-4090-9fa5-5ef5af95b4d9.description=
Adds two numbers together

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.

Returns\:
The sum of the two numbers.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

It can have value from selection list "CSA-Property-ValueType". This Input is required only when Input "onlyUpdate" is selected as "no". values - One or more values dilimited by comma , (If user want to use some other separator for multiple values then needs to be pass as next input "separator") separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the values ( default dilimiter used is comma ,) 32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.7a81fa68-e3fe-4456-83b0-41122c13bc61.prompt=Service Component Id 32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.9e9f0aeb-7a4e-458e-a280-ac8e9e428d7d.prompt=User Identifier 32fb6761-dd35-44f8-a349-6c391d2650b4.description=
Add Server Components to Server Group and Provision a clone server 

Input Parameters\:
serverGrpId - Server Group Component Id
serviceInstanceId - Service Instance Id of the Subscription
addServers - Number of Servers to be added
userIdentifier - OO Application UUID to authorize a REST Call

Responses\:
   success -  if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0
   failure - otherwise
